<s1 id=CalendarFileMenu>Calendar File Menu
	<idx>File menu<sort>file menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>File menu:Print Current View<sort>file menu:print current view<\idx> -->
	<idx>Print Current View:on File menu<sort>print current view:on file menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>File menu:Print<sort>file menu:print<\idx> -->
	<idx>Print:on File menu<sort>print:on file menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>File menu:Options<sort>file menu:options<\idx> -->
	<idx>Options:on File menu<sort>options:on file menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>File menu:Exit<sort>file menu:exit<\idx> -->
	<idx>Exit:on File menu<sort>exit:on file menu<\idx>

<newline>&empty;

<p gentity=Calendar-File-Menu gposition=left>
<newline>&empty;
<term nogloss>Print Current View<\term> prints the current calendar view on the
default printer.<newline>
<term nogloss>Print<\term> displays the Print dialog box so you can choose the
calendar view, appointment list, or To Do list to print.<newline>
<term nogloss>Options<\term> displays the Calendar options dialog box so you 
can customize some of the features of your calendar.<newline>
<term nogloss>Exit<\term> quits the Calendar application.

<s1 id=CalendarEditMenu>Calendar Edit Menu
	<idx>Edit menu<sort>edit menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Edit menu:Appointment<sort>edit menu:appointment<\idx> -->
	<idx>Appointment:on Edit menu<sort>appointment:on edit menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Edit menu:To Do<sort>edit menu:to do<\idx> -->
	<idx>To Do:on Edit menu<sort>to do:on edit menu<\idx>

<newline>&empty;

<p gentity=Calendar-Edit-Menu gposition=left>
<newline>&empty;
<term nogloss>Appointment<\term> displays the Appointment Editor, for
scheduling appointments.<newline>
<term nogloss>To Do<\term> displays the To Do Editor, for creating and
editing to do lists.<newline>

<s1 id=CalendarViewMenu>Calendar View Menu
	<idx>View menu<sort>view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:Day<sort>view menu:day<\idx> -->
	<idx>Day:on View menu<sort>day:on view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:Week<sort>view menu:week<\idx> -->
	<idx>Week:on View menu<sort>week:on view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:Month<sort>view menu:month<\idx> -->
	<idx>Month:on View menu<sort>month:on view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:Year<sort>view menu:year<\idx> -->
	<idx>Year:on View menu<sort>year:on view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:Appointment List<sort>view menu:appointment list<\idx> -->
	<idx>Appointment List:on View menu<sort>appointment list:on view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:To Do List<sort>view menu:to do list<\idx> -->
	<idx>To Do List:on View menu<sort>to do list:on view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:Find<sort>view menu:find<\idx> -->
	<idx>Find:on View menu<sort>find:on view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:Go to Date<sort>view menu:go to date<\idx> -->
	<idx>Go to Date:on View menu<sort>go to date:on view menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>View menu:Time Zone<sort>view menu:time zone<\idx> -->
	<idx>Time Zone:on View menu<sort>time zone:on view menu<\idx>

<newline>&empty;

<p gentity=Calendar-View-Menu gposition=left>
<newline>&empty;
<term nogloss>Day<\term> changes the view to display the 
selected day.<newline>
<term nogloss>Week<\term> changes the view to display the 
selected week.<newline>
<term nogloss>Month<\term> changes the view to display the 
selected month.<newline>
<term nogloss>Year<\term> changes the view to display the 
selected year.<newline>
<term nogloss>Appointment List<\term> displays the Appointment List 
for the current view.<newline>
<term nogloss>To Do List<\term> displays the To Do list 
for the current view.<newline>
<term nogloss>Find<\term> displays the Find dialog box so you can 
search for an appointment in your calendar.<newline>
<term nogloss>Go to Date<\term> displays the Go to Date dialog box so
you can enter a date to view (default format is MM/DD/YYYY).<newline>
<term nogloss>Time Zone<\term> displays a list of time zones to choose 
from if you want to view a calendar in another time zone.


<s1 id=CalendarBrowseMenu>Calendar Browse Menu
	<idx>Browse menu<sort>browse menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Browse menu:Show Other Calendar<sort>browse menu:show other calendar<\idx> -->
	<idx>Show Other Calendar:on Browse menu<sort>show other calendar:on browse menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Browse menu:Compare Calendars<sort>browse menu:compare calendars<\idx> -->
	<idx>Compare Calendars:on Browse menu<sort>compare calendars:on browse menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Browse menu:Menu Editor<sort>browse menu:menu editor<\idx> -->
	<idx>Menu Editor:on Browse menu<sort>menu editor:on browse menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Browse menu:<emph>calendar-name@hostname<\emph> entries<sort>browse menu:calendar-name@hostname entries<\idx> -->
	<idx>calendar-name@hostname:on Browse menu<sort>calendar-name@hostname:on browse menu<\idx>

<newline>&empty;

<p gentity=Calendar-Browse-Menu gposition=left>
<term nogloss>Show Other Calendar<\term> displays the Show Other Calendar
dialog box so you can view another calendar. 
Calendar names are in the format 
<emph>calendar-name@hostname<\emph>.<newline>
<term nogloss>Compare Calendars<\term> displays the Compare Calendars dialog 
box so you can display selected calendars from the Browse list one on top 
of another in a grid. Compare Calendars helps you find a free block of 
time for a group appointment.<newline>
<term nogloss>Menu Editor<\term> displays the Menu Editor so you
can add calendars to the Browse list to browse or compare.<newline>
<term nogloss>calendar-name@hostname<\term> entries form the list of 
calendars to browse or compare.  Add calendars that you browse or
compare often to the Browse list using the Menu Editor.


<s1 id=CalendarHelpMenu>Calendar Help Menu
	<idx>Help menu<sort>help menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Help menu:Overview<sort>help menu:overview<\idx> -->
	<idx>Overview:on Help menu<sort>overview:on help menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Help menu:Tasks<sort>help menu:tasks<\idx> -->
	<idx>Tasks:on Help menu<sort>tasks:on help menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Help menu:Reference<sort>help menu:reference<\idx> -->
	<idx>Reference:on Help menu<sort>reference:on help menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Help menu:On Item<sort>help menu:on item<\idx> -->
	<idx>On Item:on Help menu<sort>on item:on help menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Help menu:Using Help<sort>help menu:using help<\idx> -->
	<idx>Using Help:on Help menu<sort>using help:on help menu<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Help menu:About <emph>application<\emph><sort>help menu:about application<\idx> -->
	<idx>About <emph>application<\emph>:on Help menu<sort>about application:on help menu<\idx>

<newline>&empty;

<!-- Here is Calendar's Help menu with commands for requesting specific  -->
<!-- kinds of help. -->

<p gentity=Calendar-Help-Menu gposition=left>
<term nogloss>Overview<\term> displays introductory information 
about Calendar features.<newline>
<term nogloss>Tasks<\term> displays step-by-step instructions for using 
Calendar.<newline>
<term nogloss>Reference<\term> displays summary information about 
Calendar components.<newline>
<term nogloss>On Item<\term> changes the pointer to a question mark--click the 
question mark pointer on a Calendar item for its description.<newline>
<term nogloss>Using Help<\term> displays information about using Help.<newline>
<term nogloss>About Calendar<\term> displays version and copyright 
information about Calendar.

	
<s1 id=CalendarToolBar>Calendar Tool Bar
<!--	<location id=CalendarApptButton>&empty;<\location> -->
<!--	<location id=CalendarTodoButton>&empty;<\location> -->
<!--	<location id=CalendarPrevButton>&empty;<\location> -->
<!--	<location id=CalendarTodayButton>&empty;<\location> -->
<!--	<location id=CalendarNextButton>&empty;<\location> -->
<!--	<location id=CalendarDayButton>&empty;<\location> -->
<!--	<location id=CalendarWeekButton>&empty;<\location> -->
<!--	<location id=CalendarMonthButton>&empty;<\location> -->
<!--	<location id=CalendarYearButton>&empty;<\location> -->

	<idx>Tool bar<sort>tool bar<\idx>
	<idx>icons:Calendar<sort>icons:calendar<\idx>
	<idx>Calendar icons<sort>calendar icons<\idx>

<newline>&empty;

The Calendar tool bar provides the following controls:

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Tool-Bar>
<\figure>

<!--	<idx>Tool bar:Appointment Editor icon<sort>tool bar:appointment editor icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>Appointment Editor icon:in Tool bar<sort>appointment editor icon:in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons:Appointment Editor<sort>calendar icons:appointment editor<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons:Appointment Editor<sort>icons:appointment editor<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-ApptEd-Icon ghyperlink=appt-ed glinktype=Definition>
Use the Appointment Editor to add, delete, and edit appointments 
on your calendar, and set reminders, repeat interval, and privacy level 
for individual appointments.
To see what the Appointment Editor looks like, click on its icon.

<!--	<idx>Tool bar:To Do Editor icon<sort>tool bar:to do editor icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>To Do Editor icon:in Tool bar<sort>to do editor icon:in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons:To Do Editor<sort>calendar icons:to do editor<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons:To Do Editor<sort>icons:to do editor<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-ToDoEd-Icon ghyperlink=todo-ed glinktype=Definition>
Use the To Do Editor to add, delete, and edit To Do items on 
your calendar, and set reminders and a repeat interval for 
individual To Do items.
To see what the To Do Editor looks like, click on its icon.

<!--	<idx>Tool bar, Previous view icon<sort>tool bar, previous view icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>Previous view icon, in Tool bar<sort>previous view icon, in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons, Previous view<sort>calendar icons, previous view<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons, Previous view<sort>icons, previous view<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-Prev-View>
The left-facing arrow changes the view
displayed in the calendar to the previous view.  For example, if you
are viewing by month, clicking the left-facing arrow displays
the previous month.

<!--	<idx>Tool bar, Today icon<sort>tool bar, today icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>Today icon, in Tool bar<sort>today icon, in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons, Today<sort>calendar icons, today<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons, Today<sort>icons, today<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-Today>
The Today button changes the calendar display
to the current day in the format you are viewing.
For example, if you are viewing by month, clicking Today
displays the current month.

<!--	<idx>Tool bar, Next view icon<sort>tool bar, next view icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>Next view icon, in Tool bar<sort>next view icon, in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons, Next view<sort>calendar icons, next view<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons, Next view<sort>icons, next view<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-Next-View>
The right-facing arrow changes the view  
displayed in the calendar to the next view.  For example, if you
are viewing by month, clicking the right-facing arrow displays
the next month.

<!--	<idx>Tool bar, Day view icon<sort>tool bar, day view icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>Day view icon, in Tool bar<sort>day view icon, in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons, Day view<sort>calendar icons, day view<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons, Day view<sort>icons, day view<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-Day-Icon ghyperlink=day-button glinktype=Definition>
The Day view icon displays the calendar you are viewing with a single day's 
appointments In the window.  Day view also provides a three-month mini-calendar
for reference and navigation, which displays the month you are viewing
and the previous and next months.  
To see what Day view looks like, click on its icon.

<!--	<idx>Tool bar, Week view icon<sort>tool bar, week view icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>Week view icon, in Tool bar<sort>week view icon, in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons, Week view<sort>calendar icons, week view<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons, Week view<sort>icons, week view<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-Week-Icon ghyperlink=week-button glinktype=Definition>
The Week view icon displays the calendar you are viewing with a week's 
appointments in the window.  
In week view, a grid is displayed showing shaded areas where appointments are
scheduled.
To see what Week view looks like, click on its icon.

<!--	<idx>Tool bar, Month view icon<sort>tool bar, month view icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>Month view icon, in Tool bar<sort>month view icon, in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons, Month view<sort>calendar icons, month view<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons, Month view<sort>icons, month view<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-Month-Icon ghyperlink=month-button glinktype=Definition>
The Month view icon displays the calendar you are viewing 
with a month's appointments in the window.
To see what Month view looks like, click on its icon.

<!--	<idx>Tool bar, Year view icon<sort>tool bar, year view icon<\idx> -->
	<idx>Year view icon, in Tool bar<sort>year view icon, in tool bar<\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Calendar icons, Year view<sort>calendar icons, year view<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>icons, Year view<sort>icons, year view<\idx> -->

<p indent gentity=Calendar-Year-Icon ghyperlink=year-button glinktype=Definition>
The Year view icon displays the calendar you are viewing with a year in the 
window.  Appointments are not displayed.
To see what Year view looks like, click on its icon.

