<s1 id=CalendarPrintDialog>Calendar Print Dialog Box
	<idx>Print dialog box, reference<sort>print dialog box, reference<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Print dialog box:Printer Name field<sort>print dialog box:printer name field<\idx> -->
	<idx>Printer Name field, in Print dialog box<sort>printer name field, in print dialog box<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Print dialog box:Copies field<sort>print dialog box:copies field<\idx> -->
	<idx>Copies field, in Print dialog box<sort>copies field, in print dialog box<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Print dialog box:Report Type menu<sort>print dialog box:report type menu<\idx> -->
	<idx>Report Type menu, in Print dialog box<sort>report type menu, in print dialog box<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Print dialog box:From/To fields<sort>print dialog box:from to field<\idx> -->
	<idx>From/To fields, in Print dialog box<sort>from to fields, in print dialog box<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Print dialog box:Print Command Options field<sort>print dialog box:print command options field<\idx> -->
	<idx>Print Command Options, in Print dialog box<sort>print command options, in print dialog box<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Print dialog box:Print to File setting<sort>print dialog box:print to file setting<\idx> -->
	<idx>Print to File setting, in Print dialog box<sort>print to file setting, in print dialog box<\idx>
<!--	<idx>Print dialog box:Print button<sort>print dialog box:print button<\idx> -->
	<idx>Print button, in Print dialog box<sort>print button, in print dialog box<\idx>

<newline>&empty;

Use the Print dialog box to choose the Calendar view, Appointment
List, or To Do List to print.

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Print>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<lablist nowrap>
\ Printer Name \ 
                The printer on which you want to print
		a Calendar view, Appointment List, or To Do List.

\ Copies \      Number of copies of the selected view to print.

\ Report Type \ 
                Choose to print Day View, Week View, Month View, or Year View, 
		plus Appointment List or To Do List.

\ From/To \	The dates for which you want to print calendar data.
		For example, if you want to print the year view containing
		August 5, 1994, enter that date into both the From and To
		fields.  
 
\ Print Command Options \
		Printer command-line options.  For example, 
		<computer>-o nobanner<\computer>
		causes header pages to be suppressed.
		
\ Print to File \ 
		When selected, prints the selected view in a PostScript; file.

\ Print \	Prints the selected view.

\ Cancel \	Closes the dialog box.

\ Help \	Displays help for this dialog box.

<\lablist>

