<s1 id=CalendarOptionsAccessDialog>Calendar Access List and Permissions Dialog Box
	<idx>Access List and Permissions dialog box, reference<sort>reference, access list and permissions dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>User Name field, in Access List and Permissions dialog box<sort>user name field, in access list and permissions dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Add Name button, in Access List and Permissions dialog box<sort>add name button, in access list and permissions dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Access List, in Access List and Permissions dialog box<sort>access list, in access list and permissions dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Remove Name button, in Access List and Permissions dialog box<sort>remove name button, in access list and permissions dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>Permissions settings, in Access List and Permissions dialog box<sort>permissions settings, in access list and permissions dialog box<\idx>
	<idx>list, access<\idx>
	<idx>world, refers to all users <\idx> 
	<idx>access list, world reference <\idx> 
<!--	<idx>Access List and Permissions dialog box:User Name field<sort>access list and permissions dialog box:user name field<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>Access List and Permissions dialog box:Add Name button<sort>access list and permissions dialog box:add name button<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>Access List and Permissions dialog box:Access List<sort>access list and permissions dialog box:access list<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>Access List and Permissions dialog box:Remove Name button<sort>access list and permissions dialog box:remove name button<\idx> -->
<!--	<idx>Access List and Permissions dialog box:Permissions settings<sort>access list and permissions dialog box:permissions settings<\idx> -->

<newline>&empty;

<p>The Options dialog box is displayed when you choose Options from the 
File menu.  Choose Access List and Permissions from the Category menu in the 
Options dialog box to determine the access other users have to your calendar.

<note>Depending on the version of Calendar you have, you'll see one of the 
following Access List and Permissions dialog boxes.  Use the description that
applies to your installation.
<\note>

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Access>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<lablist nowrap>
\ User Name \	The name and system (<emph>username@hostname<\emph>) 
		of the user to whom you want to grant access.

\ Add Name \	Adds the user in the User Name field to the Access List.

\ Access List \	The scrolling list of users and the access to your
		calendar that you've granted to them.
		The user called "world" means everyone.

\ Remove Name \	Removes the selected user from the Access List.

\ Permissions \	Three levels of access to your calendar 
		that you can grant to others.  You can choose more
		than one permission.

<lablist>
\Browse\	Browse (the default) allows users to look at your calendar.
		You can set how much information they can see with the Privacy
		setting.  You can remove Browse access for selected users
		using the Menu Editor.
\Insert\	Permission for others to insert
		appointments on your calendar.
\Delete\	Permission for others to delete
		appointments on your calendar.
<\lablist>

<\lablist>

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Access-Alternate>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<lablist nowrap>
\ User Name \	The name and system (<emph>username@hostname<\emph>) 
		of the user to whom you want to grant access.

\ Access Rights \	The access to your appointments you grant to
			specific other users.
<lablist>

\ Public \	Access to all your appointments marked Others See Time and Text.
\ Semiprivate \	Access to all your appointments marked Others See Time and Text
		or Others See Time Only.
\ Private \	Access to all your appointments, including those marked 
		Others See Nothing.

<\lablist>
\ Permissions \	Three levels of access to your calendar 
		that you can grant to others.  You can choose more
		than one permission.

<lablist>
\View\		Permission for others to look at the appointments with the
		privacy level (public, semiprivate, or private) that 
		you've designated.
\Insert\	Permission for others to insert on your calendar appointments 
		with the privacy level you've designated.
\Change\	Permission for others to change on your calendar 
		(including deleting) appointments
		with the privacy level you've designated.
<\lablist>

\ Add \		Adds the user in the User Name field to the Access List.
\ Delete \	Deletes the selected user from the Access List.
\ Change \	Updates access for the selected user.

\ Access List \	The scrolling list of users.
		Select a user in the Access list to see his or her access.
		The user called "world" means everyone.

<\lablist>

<p>You can change the settings for individual appointments using the 
<link hyperlink=CalendarApptEditorDialog>Appointment Editor<\link>.

