<newline>&empty;

<p>The Options dialog box is displayed when you choose Options from the 
File menu.  Choose Printer Settings from the Category menu in the 
Options dialog box to determine the default printer settings for the 
Print dialog box.

<p>You can change the settings for individual print jobs using the
<link hyperlink=CalendarPrintDialog>Appointment Editor<\link>.

<newline>&empty;

<figure nonumber entity=Calendar-Printer>
<\figure>

<newline>&empty;

<lablist nowrap>

\ Destination \	Print Calendar view or list on a printer or in a file.

\ Printer \	The name of the printer on which to print a Calendar view or list.

\ Options \	Command-line printer options (such as 
		<computer>-o nobanner<\computer> to suppress the header page).

\ Width \	Horizontal size of printed image, in inches.

\ Height \	Vertical size of printed image, in inches.

\ Position \	Margins from edge of paper, in inches.

\ Units \	Numbers of consecutive Calendar views to print.  For example, if 
		you are viewing Month view for the current month and set Units to 2, 
		you will print the current month and the next month.

\ Copies \	Numbers of copies of the current view or consecutive Calendar
		views (see Units) to print.

\ Include \	Privacy level of appointments to display on your printed calendar.

<\lablist>

