		Use the date format, such as MM/DD/YYYY, set in 
		the <link hyperlink=CalendarOptionsDateDialog>Date
                Format dialog box<\link>.

\ Go To \	Changes the Calendar display to a view containing the date 
		in the 
		Date field.  For example, if you are viewing Week view and you 
		type 8/25/1997 in the Date field and click Go To, Calendar 
		displays the Week view from 8/25/1997 - 8/31/1997.  

\ Cancel \	Closes the Go To Date dialog box without changing the Calendar
		display.

